Jenna.

544
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:29,883
Jenna.

545
00:36:33,278 --> 00:36:35,497
Jenna.

546
00:36:41,329 --> 00:36:45,028
I'll kill you,
you son of a bitch!

547
00:36:50,599 --> 00:36:53,559
Honey,
you all right?

548
00:36:53,602 --> 00:36:55,256
Who did this?

549
00:36:55,300 --> 00:36:56,344
I don't know.

550
00:36:56,388 --> 00:36:59,434
Oh, god damn it,
Jenna!

551
00:36:59,478 --> 00:37:00,479
What? What?

552
00:37:00,522 --> 00:37:03,133
What are you
so mad about?

553
00:37:03,177 --> 00:37:05,701
Why didn't you
tell me about this?

554
00:37:05,745 --> 00:37:07,703
What would you
have done?

555
00:37:07,747 --> 00:37:09,749
I feel like
this complete idiot.

556
00:37:09,792 --> 00:37:11,011
Everybody knows
except me.

557
00:37:11,054 --> 00:37:13,274
What bothers you more,
Emmett,

558
00:37:13,318 --> 00:37:16,277
that I was attacked
or that you weren't told?

559
00:37:16,321 --> 00:37:18,801
I swear to god,
I don't know
anything anymore.

560
00:37:18,845 --> 00:37:21,500
What were you
doing out here
by yourself?

561
00:37:21,543 --> 00:37:23,241
Gee, that's a tough one.

562
00:37:23,284 --> 00:37:26,461
I guess it's that
I don't get nearly enough
excitement in my life.

563
00:37:26,505 --> 00:37:27,593
Oh, I get it.

564
00:37:27,636 --> 00:37:29,377
We're doing
the sarcastic
thing, huh?

565
00:37:29,421 --> 00:37:32,206
Yeah. Yeah.
It's all my fault.

566
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:33,947
I should have
told Sanders

567
00:37:33,990 --> 00:37:35,949
not to kill that student
in cold blood

568
00:37:35,992 --> 00:37:38,430
so you wouldn't have
to be so put out!

569
00:37:38,473 --> 00:37:41,650
Maybe you should
reconsider testifying.

570
00:37:42,521 --> 00:37:45,437
I mean, no one
but you is saying...

571
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,352
Go ahead, say it.

572
00:37:48,657 --> 00:37:51,007
Go ahead, Emmett.

573
00:37:52,226 --> 00:37:53,575
Say it!

574
00:37:56,230 --> 00:37:58,580
Just take me home.

575
00:38:01,714 --> 00:38:04,238
I got to stop
at the trailer

576
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:07,372
and pick up
my overnight stuff.

577
00:38:07,415 --> 00:38:09,417
I, um...

578
00:38:09,852 --> 00:38:14,204
I don't think
I want you to stay
tonight, o.K.?

579
00:38:16,729 --> 00:38:20,863
Why don't you
just drop me off at
the sheriff's office

580
00:38:20,907 --> 00:38:23,083
so I can file a report?

581
00:38:23,126 --> 00:38:24,780
Hey, fine.

582
00:38:24,824 --> 00:38:25,999
Whatever you want.

583
00:38:26,042 --> 00:38:29,263
Let's do this
your way, Jenna.

584
00:38:34,050 --> 00:38:34,921
Ha ha!

585
00:38:34,964 --> 00:38:37,315
Oh, Jenna!

586
00:38:48,108 --> 00:38:49,849
Ice...

587
00:38:49,892 --> 00:38:50,676
Hello.

588
00:38:50,719 --> 00:38:52,895
Heh heh heh
heh heh heh!

589
00:38:52,939 --> 00:38:55,594
Do you like
tormenting people?

590
00:38:55,637 --> 00:38:56,464
Suck it.

591
00:38:56,508 --> 00:38:59,249
Suck it in,
you punk.

592
00:38:59,293 --> 00:39:01,077
Yeah...

593
00:39:02,427 --> 00:39:03,210
Heh heh heh!

594
00:39:03,253 --> 00:39:05,473
It's no fun
to be afraid,

595
00:39:05,517 --> 00:39:06,648
to be tormented,

596
00:39:06,692 --> 00:39:08,607
is it?

597
00:39:08,650 --> 00:39:11,784
Oh...no.

598
00:39:11,827 --> 00:39:12,524
Go ahead.

599
00:39:12,567 --> 00:39:14,700
Now's your chance,
ice.

600
00:39:14,743 --> 00:39:16,484
Run.

601
00:39:18,530 --> 00:39:20,488
Ice...

602
00:39:24,797 --> 00:39:27,713
Ice...

603
00:39:27,756 --> 00:39:30,629
Run.

604
00:39:30,672 --> 00:39:31,412
Run.

605
00:39:31,456 --> 00:39:34,241
Uhh! Uhh! Uhh!

606
00:39:35,416 --> 00:39:37,113
Ice.

607
00:39:54,696 --> 00:39:56,350
Come on!

608
00:40:13,672 --> 00:40:15,151
[Gas hisses]

609
00:40:15,195 --> 00:40:18,720
You've been more than a bit
of a discipline problem.

610
00:40:18,764 --> 00:40:23,421
Now we're going to
have to do something
about your attitude.

611
00:40:24,117 --> 00:40:25,988
Aah! Uhh!

612
00:40:26,032 --> 00:40:27,468
Come on, man!

613
00:40:27,512 --> 00:40:28,730
Uhh! Aah!

614
00:40:28,774 --> 00:40:31,559
Aah! Let me go!

615
00:40:31,864 --> 00:40:35,998
In fact, you're on
permanent detention.

616
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:38,697
[Hiss]

617
00:40:38,740 --> 00:40:41,482
No...no...aah...

618
00:40:41,526 --> 00:40:42,527
No! No!

619
00:40:42,570 --> 00:40:43,963
Aah!

620
00:40:44,006 --> 00:40:48,097
Aah! Aah!

621
00:40:58,630 --> 00:41:01,589
School's out.

622
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:14,167
Please?

623
00:41:14,210 --> 00:41:18,432
I really need some time
by myself right now.

624
00:41:19,389 --> 00:41:22,044
Damn it, Emmett,
just leave it alone.

625
00:41:22,088 --> 00:41:25,570
I can't be with you
right now.

626
00:41:34,753 --> 00:41:37,103
I'll be right back.

627
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:55,687
What is this about?

628
00:41:56,557 --> 00:41:58,167
Shouldn't you have told
Baldwin about this?

629
00:41:58,211 --> 00:42:02,389
Nah. We get those
all the time through
the state net.

630
00:42:02,432 --> 00:42:03,738
I usually trash 'em.

631
00:42:03,782 --> 00:42:06,915
As if anything
as interesting as
a serial killer

632
00:42:06,959 --> 00:42:09,135
would ever happen
in this town.

633
00:42:09,178 --> 00:42:10,832
Well, you know
what I mean.

634
00:42:10,876 --> 00:42:12,660
No, uh,
I'm afraid I don't.

635
00:42:12,704 --> 00:42:15,445
I don't think "interesting"
is the word I'd use

636
00:42:15,489 --> 00:42:17,796
to describe
a serial murderer.

637
00:42:17,839 --> 00:42:19,101
Who asked you?

638
00:42:19,145 --> 00:42:20,102
Don't touch
my garbage.

639
00:42:20,146 --> 00:42:22,540
This is
official trash.

640
00:42:22,583 --> 00:42:25,847
Not for
civilian eyes.

641
00:43:37,484 --> 00:43:41,793
"I will strike a path
in death's shoes

642
00:43:41,836 --> 00:43:44,317
"until the mission
I conclude.

643
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:46,754
"Until the mission
I conclude.

644
00:43:46,798 --> 00:43:50,105
"No sorrows or regret.

645
00:43:50,149 --> 00:43:53,979
"Death is my mission.

646
00:43:54,022 --> 00:43:55,284
"My mission...

647
00:43:55,328 --> 00:43:57,243
Is met."

648
00:44:03,379 --> 00:44:06,034
"The enemy is before me,

649
00:44:06,078 --> 00:44:08,863
"around me and yet...

650
00:44:08,907 --> 00:44:11,474
No fear will I have."

651
00:44:13,738 --> 00:44:15,914
Pass it up, man.

652
00:44:17,959 --> 00:44:20,919
Whoo! Hey!

653
00:44:22,224 --> 00:44:24,052
What's up, man?

654
00:44:24,096 --> 00:44:26,794
Hey, what's happening?

655
00:45:23,677 --> 00:45:28,421
All right,
you little shit,
no more fucking around.

656
00:45:28,464 --> 00:45:29,770
You listen to me.

657
00:45:29,814 --> 00:45:34,079
You come near Jenna,
you're going to wind up dead.

658
00:45:34,122 --> 00:45:35,123
Got it?

659
00:45:35,167 --> 00:45:36,951
Good.

660
00:46:01,628 --> 00:46:03,848
Hey, Emmett,
you ready to go?

661
00:46:03,891 --> 00:46:07,416
Hey-o, Tom,
I'll be right with you.

662
00:46:15,990 --> 00:46:17,426
[Bang]

663
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:20,342
Tom, Tom,
don't use the gun.

664
00:46:20,386 --> 00:46:22,823
It's got
the gasoline balls

665
00:46:22,867 --> 00:46:24,607
I made up
as an experiment.

666
00:46:24,651 --> 00:46:27,088
I just wanted
to clear them out

667
00:46:27,132 --> 00:46:29,743
before the kids
got here.

668
00:46:40,841 --> 00:46:43,104
Let's go to the bunker.

669
00:46:43,452 --> 00:46:46,847
Emmett,
will you slow down?
You're killing me.

670
00:46:46,891 --> 00:46:49,241
This stuff's heavy.

671
00:46:56,509 --> 00:46:58,511
Thank you.

672
00:47:06,780 --> 00:47:10,915
How far are we
from the trailers,
about half a mile?

673
00:47:10,958 --> 00:47:12,003
Yeah.

674
00:47:12,046 --> 00:47:13,134
I don't know.

675
00:47:13,178 --> 00:47:16,616
It seems close.
The kids might
find it.

676
00:47:16,659 --> 00:47:19,097
No, they won't.

677
00:47:22,317 --> 00:47:24,102
[Tapping]

678
00:47:24,145 --> 00:47:26,974
A concrete bunker
and a wooden door?

679
00:47:27,018 --> 00:47:31,196
I got a metal one
coming from Sacramento.

680
00:47:44,209 --> 00:47:50,519
So, Emmett,
what'd you do last night?
Watch TV, huh?

681
00:47:55,437 --> 00:47:58,049
All right,
I gave Sanders
a little hell.

682
00:47:58,092 --> 00:48:00,094
Do your goddamn
job right...

683
00:48:00,138 --> 00:48:02,575
What do you want me
to do?

684
00:48:02,618 --> 00:48:03,968
Can't arrest Sanders
for anything.

685
00:48:04,011 --> 00:48:06,405
He hasn't done anything,
really.

686
00:48:06,448 --> 00:48:08,102
A lot of stuff.

687
00:48:08,146 --> 00:48:11,497
Yeah. Buying military stuff
for the museum sure does
accumulate.

688
00:48:11,540 --> 00:48:13,803
How many of these
armor suits you got?

689
00:48:13,847 --> 00:48:17,938
I could use one.
I wouldn't mind
being bulletproof.

690
00:48:17,982 --> 00:48:19,113
Extra small. Surplus.

691
00:48:19,157 --> 00:48:21,811
Barely fit the mannequin
at the museum.

692
00:48:21,855 --> 00:48:23,988
Wouldn't even fit you close.

693
00:48:24,031 --> 00:48:26,207
Hey, what's this?

694
00:48:27,165 --> 00:48:28,253
Tom, don't touch that.

695
00:48:28,296 --> 00:48:30,255
This is
a suicide detonator.

696
00:48:30,298 --> 00:48:32,213
Once it's armed,
it's armed.

697
00:48:32,257 --> 00:48:34,999
You mean you can't
turn it off?

698
00:48:35,042 --> 00:48:36,174
That's right.

699
00:48:36,217 --> 00:48:37,044
Oops.

700
00:48:37,088 --> 00:48:38,393
Right, oops.

701
00:48:38,437 --> 00:48:41,005
All right,
how's it look?
Everything look secure?

702
00:48:41,048 --> 00:48:42,049
Yeah.

703
00:48:42,093 --> 00:48:44,051
O.k., let's go.

704
00:48:45,052 --> 00:48:47,098
Come on, let's go!

705
00:49:00,111 --> 00:49:01,721
Hi. How are you today?

706
00:49:01,764 --> 00:49:07,118
I wanted to tell you
I'm really enjoying
that book you gave me.

707
00:49:07,161 --> 00:49:08,510
You seem surprised.

708
00:49:08,554 --> 00:49:10,991
To tell you
the truth, I am.

709
00:49:11,035 --> 00:49:13,820
I wanted to ask you
about something.

710
00:49:13,863 --> 00:49:14,995
It's about
the dedication.

711
00:49:15,039 --> 00:49:19,043
I bought it
at a used book store.

712
00:49:25,266 --> 00:49:27,138
Hey, wait up!

713
00:49:28,966 --> 00:49:32,665
Do you know
ray Buchanan
from another school?

714
00:49:32,708 --> 00:49:34,058
No.

715
00:50:23,498 --> 00:50:26,110
Let's go get Emmett.

716
00:50:26,153 --> 00:50:31,332
Mike, get on the horn.
Get forensics down here
right away.

717
00:50:34,248 --> 00:50:38,252
Let me have
that license plate scanner.

718
00:51:12,199 --> 00:51:18,858
Damn, Emmett,
you should have stuck
to shooting at fires.

719
00:51:41,968 --> 00:51:45,102
I didn't hear you come in.

720
00:51:45,145 --> 00:51:48,975
I was really...
Lost in space.

721
00:51:49,018 --> 00:51:50,411
I just heard
they arrested Emmett

722
00:51:50,455 --> 00:51:54,589
for the murder of the boy
who attacked me last night.

723
00:51:56,200 --> 00:51:57,288
To tell the truth,

724
00:51:57,331 --> 00:52:02,597
the thing that has me
most worried is...

725
00:52:02,641 --> 00:52:08,473
That I think Emmett
is totally capable
of killing that boy.

726
00:52:09,474 --> 00:52:12,955
It's a pretty scary thought.

727
00:52:16,394 --> 00:52:18,961
I don't know what to do.

728
00:52:19,005 --> 00:52:21,790
I'm not sure
I understand you.

729
00:52:21,834 --> 00:52:23,705
Never mind.

730
00:52:23,749 --> 00:52:27,492
I have to go to the jail.

731
00:52:31,452 --> 00:52:34,629
Will you come with me?

732
00:52:40,461 --> 00:52:41,636
He didn't suffer any.

733
00:52:41,680 --> 00:52:46,598
Doc said his neck broke,
didn't feel a thing.

734
00:52:47,468 --> 00:52:49,340
I want to see Emmett.

735
00:52:49,383 --> 00:52:50,645
No chance.

736
00:52:50,689 --> 00:52:51,864
Why not?

737
00:52:51,907 --> 00:52:54,432
What do you suppose
he's in here for?

738
00:52:54,475 --> 00:52:56,651
Because of me?
It's my fault?

739
00:52:56,695 --> 00:53:01,047
If he killed that boy,
he didn't kill him
for anybody else.

740
00:53:01,090 --> 00:53:02,701
You said
it was an accident.

741
00:53:02,744 --> 00:53:04,572
We're not talking
about him.

742
00:53:04,616 --> 00:53:07,619
Ray just fell
off his bike,
Mrs. Buchanan.

743
00:53:07,662 --> 00:53:10,187
Ray Buchanan is dead?

744
00:53:11,144 --> 00:53:12,406
[Knock knock]

745
00:53:12,450 --> 00:53:15,714
The man you arrested
for the murder of the kid...

746
00:53:15,757 --> 00:53:16,845
What about him?

747
00:53:16,889 --> 00:53:19,239
How long
have you known him?

748
00:53:19,283 --> 00:53:20,371
Who are you?

749
00:53:20,414 --> 00:53:22,590
You should've got
a bulletin yesterday.

750
00:53:22,634 --> 00:53:24,636
Suddenly you got
a lot of dead kids.

751
00:53:24,679 --> 00:53:27,204
Only one of them's
a homicide.

752
00:53:27,247 --> 00:53:29,989
Is the man you arrested
a teacher?

753
00:53:30,032 --> 00:53:32,165
No.
What are you so
interest--

754
00:53:32,209 --> 00:53:34,559
hey, wait
just one minute.

755
00:53:34,602 --> 00:53:36,082
Hey, pal!

756
00:53:36,125 --> 00:53:38,389
Ash!

757
00:53:38,737 --> 00:53:41,130
G.d. Ash.

758
00:53:41,653 --> 00:53:42,610
Hey!

759
00:53:42,654 --> 00:53:44,699
What's going on?

760
00:53:47,049 --> 00:53:48,747
Had to be sure.

761
00:53:48,790 --> 00:53:50,966
What are you
talking about?

762
00:53:51,010 --> 00:53:53,578
That's classified,
sheriff, but, uh,

763
00:53:53,621 --> 00:53:57,234
thank you for
your cooperation.

764
00:54:01,020 --> 00:54:04,763
I'm not going to forget
about this, Tom.

765
00:54:05,024 --> 00:54:06,721
I know you're pissed,
Emmett,

766
00:54:06,765 --> 00:54:10,682
but I just couldn't
take a chance on this.

767
00:54:10,725 --> 00:54:12,074
I'm really sorry.

768
00:54:12,118 --> 00:54:13,641
By the way,
Jenna's here.

769
00:54:13,685 --> 00:54:19,125
I'll send her back
if you can keep civil
for five minutes.

770
00:54:55,292 --> 00:54:57,729
Ahem. Emmett.

771
00:54:58,686 --> 00:55:00,819
I'm letting you out.

772
00:55:01,298 --> 00:55:03,648
Jeff Patterson
down at the Daisy Mae

773
00:55:03,691 --> 00:55:06,128
verified you were there
all night.

774
00:55:06,172 --> 00:55:08,783
I said he would.

775
00:55:09,436 --> 00:55:10,785
Oh, it's getting late.

776
00:55:10,829 --> 00:55:13,962
Hold up.
I'll give you a ride.

777
00:55:15,181 --> 00:55:17,488
Come on, Emmett.

778
00:55:17,531 --> 00:55:19,794
Emmett! Wait!

779
00:55:19,838 --> 00:55:22,362
[Telephone rings]

780
00:55:22,406 --> 00:55:23,320
[Ring]

781
00:55:23,363 --> 00:55:26,105
Sheriff's office.
Yost speaking.

782
00:55:26,540 --> 00:55:28,716
Yeah. Hi, honey.

783
00:55:29,108 --> 00:55:30,239
They're doing what?

784
00:55:30,283 --> 00:55:34,809
Well, stop peeping
out the window at them.

785
00:55:38,944 --> 00:55:42,687
I got to go.
I got to catch up
with Emmett.

786
00:55:42,730 --> 00:55:44,036
I didn't say that.

787
00:55:44,079 --> 00:55:47,822
I didn't say that Emmett's
more important than you.

788
00:55:54,612 --> 00:55:56,265
Whoo whoo whoo whoo!

789
00:55:56,309 --> 00:55:57,049
Yeah!

790
00:55:57,092 --> 00:55:58,790
Hey, pretty boy!

791
00:55:58,833 --> 00:56:01,532
What's up, punk?

792
00:56:03,011 --> 00:56:06,667
Party at miss mckensie's!

793
00:56:06,711 --> 00:56:07,755
Jenna!

794
00:56:07,799 --> 00:56:10,279
Jenna!

795
00:56:21,813 --> 00:56:24,816
Where'd you
disappear to?

796
00:56:25,817 --> 00:56:28,776
Never mind.
I'm glad you're here.

797
00:56:28,820 --> 00:56:30,735
I came to get my book.

798
00:56:30,778 --> 00:56:33,955
I almost hate
to give it up.

799
00:56:33,999 --> 00:56:38,917
Things have been
so...Strange
and confused lately--

800
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:43,312
Emmett being
accused of being
a serial killer.

801
00:56:43,356 --> 00:56:49,101
I mean,
they might as well
have accused you or me.

802
00:56:50,885 --> 00:56:52,757
After all,
we're both teachers.

803
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:55,803
We both knew
the students who died.

804
00:56:55,847 --> 00:56:59,677
You even knew ray from
another school, right?

805
00:56:59,720 --> 00:57:02,897
I told you before
I didn't know him.

806
00:57:02,941 --> 00:57:05,378
May I please
have my book?

807
00:57:07,902 --> 00:57:10,905
These poems
are inspirational.

808
00:57:11,689 --> 00:57:14,387
